Problem:- Daily Temperatures

Given an array of integers temperatures represents the daily temperatures, return an array answer such that answer[i] is the number of days you have to wait after the ith day to get a warmer temperature. If there is no future day for which this is possible, keep answer[i] == 0 instead.

Example 1:

Input: temperatures = [73,74,75,71,69,72,76,73]
Output: [1,1,4,2,1,1,0,0]

Solution :-

Daily Temperatures finds days to wait for warmer temperature using monotonic stack. Next greater element classic.

#Java Implementation (Monotonic Stack)

class Solution {
    public int[] dailyTemperatures(int[] temperatures) {
        int[] result = new int[temperatures.length];
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();  // Indices, increasing temps
        
        for (int i = 0; i < temperatures.length; i++) {
            // Pop colder days (found warmer!)
            while (!stack.isEmpty() && 
                   temperatures[stack.peek()] < temperatures[i]) {
                int prevDay = stack.pop();
                result[prevDay] = i - prevDay;
            }
            
            // Push current day
            stack.push(i);
        }
        
        return result;
    }
}

Monotonic increasing stack: Pop when warmer temp found.

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stack: Indices of decreasing temperatures (waiting days)
For each day i:
While stack.top < current temp: Pop → set result[prev] = i-prev
Push i (waiting for warmer)
Unpopped: result[i] = 0 (no warmer day)
Trace: [73,74,75,71,69,72,76,73]

text
i=0(73): stack=[0]
i=1(74): 73<74 → result[0]=1, stack=[1]
i=2(75): 74<75 → result[1]=1, stack=[2]  
i=3(71): stack=[2,3]
i=6(76): 71<76,75<76 → result[3]=3, result[2]=4, stack=[6]
Final: [1,1,4,2,1,1,0,0] ✓

#Thought Process
Brute O(n²): Scan forward → TLE.

Monotonic stack genius:
text
Stack holds "waiting" days (decreasing temps)
Warmer day = pop all colder previous days
Each index pushed/popped ONCE = O(n)
Right-to-left intuition:

text
Process right→left: track NEXT greater
Here: left→right, stack finds next greater
Time: O(n), Space: O(n)

#Edge Cases
No warmer: [1,1,1] → [0,0,0]
Strictly increasing: [1,2,3] → [1,1,0]
Strictly decreasing: [3,2,1] → [0,0,0]
Single day: [1] → [0]
